      <h2>What is a nebula?</h2>
      <p>A nebula is the birthplace of stars!</br></br> Made up of cosmic dust and gases, these ingredients will condense and form stars. Coming in all shapes, sizes, and colors; nebulae (plural) have been growing and birthing stars since the beginning of time and the universe!</p></br></br>
      <iframe id="video" width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0MzWiKjSr9I" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>

    <div id="div2">
      <h2>NebulaNet: Who We Are</h2>
      <p>We are a cosmic farming firm.</br></br> We have partnered with NASA and ESA to bring  the unreachable sky to your home!</p> <h4> How does <b>that</b> work?</h4> <p>Our highly advanced AI robots were sent out 2 years ago to reach the closest nebula (Helix - 700 lightyears away from Earth). They have been gathering gases and cosmic dust at the nebula, and condensing them into miniature stars you can use to power your home for the rest of your life! Our super efficient and speedy UAVs will pick up your order from the Helix nebula AI robots and shoot them to your home in just over a year!</p></br></br>
    </div>

